<h2>The Dispatch Project</h2>
<br>
	<div id="myCarousel" class="carousel slide">

	    <div class="carousel-inner">
	      <div class="item">
	      	<%= image_tag("sneakernet.png", :style => "display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;display: block; ") %>
	        <div class="carousel-caption">
	          <h4>Speak Up</h4>
	          <p>We are building a "sneakernet" to allow people to avoid censorship, from internet restrictions to device confiscation.</p>
	        </div>
	      </div>
	      <div class="item">
	      	<%= image_tag("SecureCom.png", :style => "display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;display: block; ") %>
	        <div class="carousel-caption">
	          <h4>Secure Source-Journalist Communication</h4>
	          <p>Dispatch offers secure communication between sources and journalists. In addition, to help with source protection, it gives trusted virtual identities to journalists to be recognized, and for sources to build trust.</p>
	        </div>
	      </div>
	      <div class="item">
	      	<%= image_tag("publish.png", :style => "display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;display: block; ") %>
	        <div class="carousel-caption">
	          <h4>Publish</h4>
	          <p>From Dispatch, you can publish on different media platforms directly or after editotial review.</p>
	        </div>
	      </div>
	      <div class="item active">
	      	<%= image_tag("time.jpg", :style => "display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;display: block; ") %>
	        <div class="carousel-caption">
	          <h4>What is Dispatch?</h4>
	          <p>Dispatch is a publishing tool for citizen journalists in conflict areas.</p>
	        </div>
	      </div>
	    </div>
	    <a class="left carousel-control" href="#myCarousel" data-slide="prev">‹</a>
	    <a class="right carousel-control" href="#myCarousel" data-slide="next">›</a>
</div>
